


translate English day4_hk_F_7f804a31:


    nar "It's the priest from the Academics Department who gave off those weird vibes. I think her name is Lavien Rose. "


translate English day4_hk_F_7cd82938:


    nar "I got some good information from her. It might not have meant much to her, but it's an important clue in answering a question I've been pondering for a while now."


translate English day4_hk_F_22b6b2a9:


    nar "First, it seems like Vestis can alter a person's nature and psyche. Second, I'm not the only one who gets weird vibes from her."


translate English day4_hk_F_6fa02c62:


    nar "My heart begins to race as my footsteps quicken, though I stop right outside the workplace."


translate English day4_hk_F_43991393:


    nar "Securett's here. Apparently on his way back, his look of surprise is quickly replaced by a scowl, his eyes boring eyes into me."


translate English day4_hk_F_7cab32a3:


    nar "Ugh, seriously. I wasn't expecting to run into this jerk again today."


translate English day4_hk_F_1c5afa37:


    sc "Heading to the workplace?"


translate English day4_hk_F_b799a671:


    nar "It's not like him to initiate conversation, though there's a lack of warmth that's usually included in a greeting or inquiry into one's health. "


translate English day4_hk_F_16020d3a:


    nar "My mood takes a turn for the worse hearing the caution in his voice, despite having done nothing to deserve it."


translate English day4_hk_F_348f87ba:


    pl "That's honestly none of your damn business, dude."


translate English day4_hk_F_80fff029:


    sc "Oh, but it is. You have a tendency to interrupt the bishop during the breaks that she so rarely gets."


translate English day4_hk_F_d9e89e28:


    pl "The bishop gets to take breaks? I've honestly never noticed..."


translate English day4_hk_F_77791284:


    sc "..."


translate English day4_hk_F_45db1007:


    pl "You probably don't realize this since you never pay attention to anyone other than yourself, but the bishop enjoys talking with me."


translate English day4_hk_F_f39d8431:


    sc "If you knew anything, you wouldn't engage in conversation with her."


translate English day4_hk_F_e1643392:


    pl "Huh? What the hell are you going on about?"


translate English day4_hk_F_b86339e2:


    sc "There are more important things for you to do than flirt with women."


translate English day4_hk_F_cb66f261:


    sc "You need to work on your immaturity. Rather, you need to learn from the mistakes you've made today so you don't repeat them in the future."


translate English day4_hk_F_fac170ef:


    pl "...Still trying to convince me everything that happened was my fault, huh?"


translate English day4_hk_F_7073f69c:


    sc "The Cleanup Department's always been understaffed... in fact, it still is."


translate English day4_hk_F_a8bb4e00:


    sc "And yet here I am, during one of the busiest times of the year, cleaning up after your inexperienced ass, unable to do my own job properly. "


translate English day4_hk_F_3675e571:


    sc "Do you know what that means?"


translate English day4_hk_F_c01a73cd:


    nar "None of this has anything to do with me. "


translate English day4_hk_F_d7266fc8:


    nar "The blame for my inability to do what needs to get done coupled with trainees repeatedly making the same mistakes lies squarely on the shoulders of our senior mentor who didn't give us enough guidance."


translate English day4_hk_F_8c2ce6a2:


    nar "If Securett's as busy as he claims to be, then why doesn't he just lock himself up somewhere and get it all done?"


translate English day4_hk_F_0093bf13:


    nar "I want to ask him why he came all the way out here just to get himself involved, but I decide to ignore his comment instead."


translate English day4_hk_F_014f13be:


    pl "Is the bishop in the workplace right now?"


translate English day4_hk_F_299f13fe:


    nar "He grows quiet for a moment, as if irritated by my attitude. He doesn't look like he's at a loss for words. "


translate English day4_hk_F_f11f9ef7:


    nar "When he looks up again, his cold gaze is boring straight at me, glaring angrily, his shoulders trembling faintly."


translate English day4_hk_F_8de6abfb:


    sc "Would you die for the Cleanup Department?"


translate English day4_hk_F_98fe3528:


    pl "Again with the outlandish remarks..."


translate English day4_hk_F_21b1aa32:


    sc "Wrong. If you really want to work here as one of her priests, then you have to be prepared to answer, \"Yes, of course!\""


translate English day4_hk_F_25c0a471:


    pl "I'm sure the bishop wouldn't approve of you badmouthing her as much as you do."


translate English day4_hk_F_494e202d:


    sc "I already told you, that kind of thinking will only get you in trouble. "


translate English day4_hk_F_fd20a0a5:


    sc "The bishop is a servant of God himself. You must be prepared to do whatever she tells you."


translate English day4_hk_F_90569be5:


    pl "On the off chance that you're serious, I'd say you've been holed up in this temple so long, you've lost your damn mind."


translate English day4_hk_F_04d8e655:


    sc "...Perhaps I have."


translate English day4_hk_F_ebbee02e:


    nar "And with that final comment, he turns and leaves the workplace."


translate English day4_hk_F_16d010e1:


    nar "Honestly, I've been praying for his departure from the moment I bumped into him, so I merely watch him leave wordlessly."


translate English day4_hk_F_9cd34b5b:


    nar "Once he's gone, I glance around the workplace but see no sign of Haku. Should I try coming back later when I know that jerk won't be here? "


translate English day4_hk_F_c9e73e02:


    nar "This was a waste of time..."


