    nvl clear


translate English day4_ar_N_a6a16996:


    "\n I stop by the Training Grounds while out on my uneasy walk only to find Arne nowhere to be seen."


translate English day4_ar_N_395f2a8a:


    "While poking around inquisitively, I'm approached by the priests from the Magic Department."


translate English day4_ar_N_448e7754:


    "It sounds like Arne has already left for business elsewhere."


translate English day4_ar_N_439c497b:


    "Although I didn't say anything, being told of Arne's absence fills me with a sense of both guilt and shame."


translate English day4_ar_N_b5eb2c2d:


    "I can't just drop in on someone as busy as her."


translate English day4_ar_N_88019d13:


    et "That's too bad. Guess I'll have to come back some other time..."


translate English day4_ar_F_cc3d27bc:


    nar "Before I open the door to the training grounds, I press my ear up against it."


translate English day4_ar_F_0d8087de:


    nar " I can't hear anything from within. I peek in, confirming my suspicions that nobody was there."


translate English day4_ar_F_68ffa828:


    nar "But apparently, the door wasn't locked. The weight of my body pushes it open. I carefully take a step through the gap."


translate English day4_ar_F_518244ba:


    er "Who's there?"


translate English day4_ar_F_633e1d13:


    pl "Ack!" with sshake


translate English day4_ar_F_ee6f6a44:


    er "Well! At this hour, I thought a burglar had set foot into this bastion of magic. If it isn't my nephew! "


translate English day4_ar_F_07b0e3e6:


    er "I decided to come see how gutsy this intruder had, but you're one guest I'm actually happy to see."


translate English day4_ar_F_fe619cc0:


    pl "O-Oh, hello, Bishop... Hahaha, sorry... I didn't realize you were here."


translate English day4_ar_F_99dafb25:


    nar "I thought nobody was here... He's so small I didn't even notice."


translate English day4_ar_F_4e88db7e:


    pl "Hmm... Is Arnie around?"


translate English day4_ar_F_1bfff32e:


    er "Arne has already returned to her room. She seemed quite tired from the day. "


translate English day4_ar_F_a4588fbd:


    er "Though if you wish, I can tell her to come down."


translate English day4_ar_F_186a3e17:


    pl "N-No, you don't have to do that! If she's tired, I'd feel bad dragging her here."


translate English day4_ar_F_98918213:


    er "Ah. Well, I can't let my nephew come all this way for nothing!"


translate English day4_ar_F_eaf6d613:


    er "The next best thing, and all that--what would you say to a chat with me instead?"


translate English day4_ar_F_9ec74aeb:


    nar "This little tanuki-faced old guy... He planned for this."


translate English day4_ar_F_82f817b5:


    pl "Well, sure... But the dorms will close soon, so I can't stay here for long."


translate English day4_ar_F_b07c2171:


    er "No need to worry. I won't take that much of your time. How have you fared of late?"


translate English day4_ar_F_3cb77895:


    pl "...No particular problems, really. I guess my bed is a little uncomfortable, so I haven't gotten that much sleep."


translate English day4_ar_F_628114b6:


    er "The furniture is old, having been used ever since the days of the old disposal team, so that does make sense."


translate English day4_ar_F_8d7ccc32:


    pl "So that was why, huh... I thought they looked pretty old for a newly-established post."


translate English day4_ar_F_16585ea6:


    er "They are suitable toys for that child who plays house wearing crowns made of folded paper."


translate English day4_ar_F_1f976fc3:


    pl "Haha... You always start talking like that when it comes to the Cleanup Department. "


translate English day4_ar_F_b72b2e96:


    pl "You know, I don't really think Bishop Haku hates you that much..."


translate English day4_ar_F_991609fb:


    er "Hrm? Did you believe I hated the girl? "


translate English day4_ar_F_bf298cd3:


    er "Of course not. She's an infantile brat. But in this case, I'm pointing my finger at the parents who raised her so recklessly."


translate English day4_ar_F_7354e332:


    er "After all, the foremost job of a parent is to take responsibility for their child."


translate English day4_ar_F_93e6927b:


    pl "Oh... Wait, you said you were an uncle. Does that mean you're not a father? You don't have any kids or anything?"


translate English day4_ar_F_a37d6c2a:


    er "Indeed not. Come, now, nephew--I am a priest at the moment anyway. Do you think a priest who has dedicated his life to God could conceive children?"


translate English day4_ar_F_463cffad:


    pl "Whoa. The temple's rules must be pretty strict..."


translate English day4_ar_F_ce30310a:


    er "That girl's face looks exactly like her father's. I saw it when she was very young, and the older she gets, the more the resemblance grows. "


translate English day4_ar_F_976d646c:


    er "He evades questions by saying she is his foster daughter, but there is little doubt she's a bastard. To think someone like that would be the temple's cardinal..."


translate English day4_ar_F_ea3917ba:


    pl "Umm... Bishop, I know it's probably rude to ask an adult this, but... How old are you?"


translate English day4_ar_F_fe87db0d:


    er "Please, no need for the formality. Anyway, I'm not that old. In fact, I just turned forty-five this year."


translate English day4_ar_F_f696abe3:


    pl "Wait, that's younger than I thought! Don't people mistake your age a lot because of the way you talk?"


translate English day4_ar_F_bec0837a:


    er "You should watch your words in front of your superior, whelp. "


translate English day4_ar_F_0fc032bd:


    er "Sigh... It bothers me every day that those who must bow to me still live comfortably with eyes unclouded."


translate English day4_ar_F_7fd93ccf:


    pl "Wow... You have it pretty rough since you're a bit older, huh?"


translate English day4_ar_F_d68d976f:


    er "They let their deaths slip away from them, and so their minds have festered. "


translate English day4_ar_F_8344f475:


    er "You seem to have much to ask. We have time, so please, be my guest."


translate English day4_ar_F_da1e7dc5:


    pl "Hmm. Well..."


translate English er_end_56b0a303:


    er "In any case, I am attempting to make decisive reforms to overturn our oudated system."


translate English er_end_efd1d7a6:


    er "That is also part of the reason I brought you here."


translate English er_end_7c4397fe:


    pl "What do you mean?"


translate English er_end_e3d389d8:


    er "I will end the marriages of close relatives, dictated since long ago, and rebuild our antiquated history."


translate English er_end_33189d6c:


    er "The rightful heir to the Alternatas marrying an outsider would be quite satisfactory for the first step in regard to such reforms."


translate English er_end_ec71c98f:


    pl "Hmm... I basically get what you're talking about. But are you sure you want to entrust your precious daughter to an outsider?"


translate English er_end_f394561e:


    er "It is to protect her."


translate English er_end_75019ae1:


    er "If she goes too long without a partner, the foolish dotards among the mages are like to lay their filthy hands on her."


translate English er_end_85f96e3c:


    pl "Wouldn't there have been other options?"


translate English er_end_1260cd09:


    er "Her other relatives amounted only to my sister and brother, both of whom have already passed."


translate English er_end_fd38e2c9:


    er "Have you understood the meaning of your position?"


translate English er_end_4b9aab1e:


    pl "I think I understand how hard you work in order to live, Bishop."


translate English er_end_2bfa81bd:


    er "Then let us bring things to a close for the day. I must soon rise and deal with my remaining tasks."


translate English er_end_9b912864:


    pl "Oh... I should be getting back too."


translate English er_end_a7c3ff83:


    er "Take care as you return--the path is dark."


translate English er_end_dd694c5c:


    nar "I close the heavy doors and leave the training grounds. If I want to see Arnie, I should probably get here a little earlier."


translate English er_end_c98d7ef6:


    nar "Because all that did was bring me a little closer to Bishop Erzsebet instead..."


translate English er_end_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English er1_f19c6a03:


    er "I am Erzsebet Alternata, thirteenth head of the Alternata family. "


translate English er1_2a0cdb74:


    er "I am currently employed at Saint Sheol as the leader of its Magic Department."


translate English er1_1b458202:


    pl "Why's your name...like that?"


translate English er1_35b4e0c2:


    er "My name...?"


translate English er1_91e686c1:


    nar "Something about what I said seems to offend him, as he breaks his relaxed manner and frowns."


translate English er1_fdaa70db:


    pl "Oh, I mean, uh... I wouldn't think a man would have that name. Is it your real name?"


translate English er1_da7a8ad1:


    er "Then let me ask you this. Why is your name \"like that,\" nephew?"


translate English er1_8389e731:


    pl "Oh. Huh? I mean, my parents gave it to me, and I'm proud of it..."


translate English er1_a3085fd1:


    er "I'm sure you are."


translate English er1_d739a2e4:


    nar "Geez...He really doesn't mince words."


translate English er1_498de7db:


    er "My name... It is fascinating, is it not?"


translate English er1_6b5eded7:


    er "Have you any guesses as to why I was given it? The eldest child of the Alternata family is always sent a divine message that misfortune will befall them."


translate English er1_bb5a59d5:


    er "This is why, whenever a child is born, they are given a name of the opposite gender."


translate English er1_c68ac9c6:


    pl "But if the message is just sent to whoever's the oldest kid, why does their gender matter?"


translate English er1_009fc60d:


    er "Apparently, others don't wish to consider daughters their children."


translate English er1_f302efc9:


    pl "Weird..."


translate English er1_3cb52756:


    er "Personally, I would prefer to give Arne a new name, "


translate English er1_18c43245:


    er "but I cannot willfully lay hands on that which was given to her by her parents. "


translate English er1_389922f9:


    er "I am sure they thought well and hard about it."


translate English er1_6244d305:


    pl "But won't misfortune come to her, then? Is that okay?"


translate English er1_b7a40f10:


    er "We must not cling to such absurd superstitions. Arne is a strong child--more than capable of determining her own fate."


translate English er2_a9b101b7:


    pl "I wanted to ask about your family."


translate English er2_81b44bb5:


    er "My family? That's a rather sudden question. "


translate English er2_6a6c34a0:


    er "It's me and Arne--as you know--as well as...one other."


translate English er2_599eeace:


    pl "I mean, since you're an uncle, well... That means you have siblings, right?"


translate English er2_9d938ed9:


    er "Ah, I understand. I was born the second of three children. "


translate English er2_616a8542:


    er "Our parents were both dull people, blinded by wealth and power. Come to think of it, I left home at about the same age as you."


translate English er2_305c92f5:


    er "Still, I had a good relationship with my older sister and younger brother."


translate English er2_7d528dc9:


    pl "Whoa. You have parents too, huh?"


translate English er2_5623ca55:


    er "Are you choosing your words specifically to irritate me?"


translate English er2_a84fba3f:


    pl "N-No! Sorry about that."


translate English er2_f89d42a7:


    er "Very well. A man of magic must be possessed of that much pluck, at least."


translate English er2_f5d83349:


    er "The youngest of us--my brother, and Arne's father--was a man filled with loyalty to his duty. "


translate English er2_d233f18e:


    er "My sister was strong, kind, and beautiful, the kind who wasn't afraid to make decisions. "


translate English er2_89c0cd57:


    er "Unfortunately, God chose to take her into His arms early. But in all my life, I have never once seen a woman as perfect as she."


translate English er2_58d3d0ce:


    pl "Not even Arnie?"


translate English er2_52d8df40:


    er "Oh, my Arne is naturally the most perfect in the world as well. I suppose children have taken after their parents since antiquity."


translate English er3_b22617da:


    pl "Well, then... I wanted to ask more about the Magic Department, just so I know what I'm getting into."


translate English er3_224f43c5:


    er "Oh? I applaud your attitude! The Magic Department exists to foster mages--the foremost of all those who live on this continent."


translate English er3_7fc04a3e:


    er "Each mage develops his own sacred techniques and provides services for the betterment of the country."


translate English er3_31b1f2e8:


    er "That makes us fitting to be lords of these lands which emphasize sacred power, does it not?"


translate English er3_52719318:


    pl "Sacred techniques...? Arnie mentioned them before. Are they like mystic arts?"


translate English er3_f22bb0d2:


    er "Any technique that is used to grant power beyond that of humans is considered a sacred technique."


translate English er3_1b286aa2:


    er "As are those which convert information into matter in the way of witches practiced by the Academics Department--as well as, in a broader sense, the skilled use of amity utilized by the Health Department."


translate English er3_ec349d39:


    er "But it is the Magic Department whose family heads protect history and tradition and who use these sacred techniques passed down for generations in order to fight. We are the proud servants of God."


translate English er3_216cf651:


    pl "Is that why you're all floaty like that?"


translate English er3_011e0f39:


    er "Having grown used to my old body, I found my low vantage point quite inconvenient."


translate English er3_0ce23fe5:


    pl "Wow, that's really amazing. Do the Alternatas specialize in making things move with their minds, then?"


translate English er3_01bc128e:


    er "What, this? No more than the most basic of the basics!"


translate English er3_53cc5468:


    er "Alternatas wear the power they inherit like clothing--a power that goes beyond physical human limits."


translate English er3_d5106d47:


    pl "That sounds so cool. I want to try!"


translate English er3_4ed584f7:


    er "Now, don't be hasty. Using sacred power without the proper preparation is reckless. Your body and mind must be able to endure it, lest you turn into a monster."


translate English er3_e456979e:


    pl "That's lame..."


translate English er3_0a217d24:


    er "God's power is not one to be borrowed and brandished for the purposes of mere passing interest! Unchecked, it can indeed lead to a person's death."


translate English er3_4da18066:


    er "Still, I did personally select you to be heir to the Alternatas. When the time comes, you shall understand it all, even if you do not wish to."


translate English er3_7b181bed:


    er "Until then, you must learn temple etiquette and train your body in mind, keeping your pride as a mage close at hand. Be ever vigilant."


translate English er3_f4cdf4e1:


    pl "Alright, alright, I gotcha. Wait. I don't think I've ever seen my current department's bishop using sacred techniques."


translate English er3_1176da4f:


    er "She is a mix, after all..."


translate English er3_fc036a19:


    er "...And she scrubs corpses every day. What would come of her using sacred techniques?"


translate English er_re_c7fa89d0:


    er "Well then. If you've any questions, ask."


translate English day4_rs_F_a9248cd4:


    nar "As I'm about to go up the stairs, I quickly change direction and go into the library instead. "


translate English day4_rs_F_2eb77d24:


    nar "If I'm going to talk to Lavien, I'd rather it be when she's fully herself."


translate English day4_rs_F_f688bd81:


    nar "Last time, I just felt creeped out, like someone was watching me the whole time. But after the accident, I've started to get the bigger picture."


translate English day4_rs_F_c287cdee:


    nar "They're probably hiding, watching me right now."


translate English day4_rs_F_78eff3e8:


    nar "No bishops come to speak to me directly, though--maybe because they'd seen me speak to the bishop directly."


translate English day4_rs_F_27eed167:


    nar "I go back into the room I just left. Thankfully, Lavien is still here."


translate English day4_rs_F_46a86efa:


    rv "Huh? Little [na]? Did you forget something?"


translate English day4_rs_F_836e349f:


    pl "No, not exactly... I just thought maybe we could have a normal chat."


translate English day4_rs_F_f1c0bf4b:


    rv "Oh? While I am quite honored that you would pick little old me, entertaining conversation is not my forte."


translate English day4_rs_F_55d1895d:


    pl "I'm fine with you just replying here and there. Were you busy?"


translate English day4_rs_F_bd012f3b:


    rv "I have the time for some light conversation. I believe this is called 'free time', yes?"


translate English day4_rs_F_6042f27c:


    rv "In any case, I do have plans to meet with Lord Enoch during lunch."


translate English day4_rs_F_21aa9473:


    pl "Enoch? I'm surprised you two know each other."


translate English day4_rs_F_1b7a04c8:


    rv "I'm very honored to. Although, here at the temple, I suspect fewer have never spoken to him than those who have. "


translate English day4_rs_F_2433f2b3:


    rv "Ah, how was the book you borrowed?"


translate English day4_rs_F_5857b895:


    pl "I haven't even opened it yet."


translate English day4_rs_F_94e0731b:


    rv "Is that so? Well, reading is best enjoyed when you have time and the mental space to spare."


translate English day4_rs_F_b5aacee4:


    rv "Grimoires are closer to reference materials than anything else, so I go at them pretty hard, like I'm trying to pound the information into my brain."


translate English day4_rs_F_539685e4:


    rv "Oh, whoopsies! That is purely how I do things. You needn't feel you must follow it."


translate English day4_rs_F_859368aa:


    pl "...Why do you seem so distressed?"


translate English day4_rs_F_75ef72cb:


    rv "Was it that easy to tell? "


translate English day4_rs_F_6318eb96:


    rv "This is my first time chatting with you, little [na]. I suppose I'm a little nervous,"


translate English day4_rs_F_9e8deb10:


    rv " though I'm embarrassed to admit such."


translate English day4_rs_F_458a2b42:


    pl "I guess even calm and collected people like you get nervous sometimes... In that case, I'll ask the questions. You just have to answer."


translate English day4_rs_F_d3ce0c02:


    rv "Then ask away."


translate English rv1_f2ca52e0:


    pl "...I see the midnight sun is still going on, hmm?"


translate English rv1_47d3cd82:


    pl "...I see the polar night is still going on, hmm?"


translate English rv1_d2b0e65c:


    rv "That's quite an odd thing to say."


translate English rv1_c194e0f4:


    pl "You said something weird first and it made me uncomfortable!"


translate English rv1_19214720:


    rv "Oopsies! I did a bad. "


translate English rv1_3789fbd8:


    rv "In that case, I will give you some simple information on the midnight sun to avoid further discomfort."


translate English rv1_52b658f0:


    rv "In that case, I will give you some simple information on the polar night to avoid further discomfort."


translate English rv1_64b07bc5:


    nar "I think I'm bored already..."


translate English rv1_5494d296:


    rv "Ahem. Many in the capital believe the polar night to be a form of divine judgment wherein the pestis's effects devour the sun. "


translate English rv1_ef18d642:


    rv "However, it is simply a natural phenomenon born from nature. Namely, our high latitude."


translate English rv1_73f9b99e:


    rv "Daytime in the capital is cold, so a polar night occurs once or twice every year. Other times, the sun won't actually set."


translate English rv1_a6be3551:


    pl "That would make it daytime all the time, right?"


translate English rv1_aa1d002c:


    rv "Yes. And we call this nightless period of time the midnight sun."


translate English rv1_c19555e9:


    rv "These are much rarer compared to polar nights. Records say they only happen once every millenium."


translate English rv1_9b59d15a:


    rv "And because its cycle aligns with the great calamity, some believe white light to be an omen of the pestis."


translate English rv1_95170398:


    pl "Does everyone in the capital hate white like that?"


translate English rv1_e1d3679c:


    rv "Well, they certainly love the color black."


translate English rv1_a516ee2d:


    rv "But I'm sure you've heard something similar at least once or twice--with your obsidian black hair being the symbol of a mage and all that."


translate English rv1_24e806da:


    pl "Urk... You make fun of me so easily."


translate English rv2_5bd6cce9:


    rv "I am Lavien Rose, auxiliary bishop of the Academics Department--despite my inexperience."


translate English rv2_e3cf4ebc:


    rv "Library searches, drainpipe repairs, speed talking, thesis writing, legal consulting... I do it all."


